My MIL lives in a nursing home. 5 weeks ago, she tested positive for COVID-19 from a routine test administered by her dialysis center (she is and remains asymptomatic). Today they called again. He asked how they got his number when she lives in a nursing home and has her own direct number. They claimed his number was listed on the test result. They also claimed not to know she was living in a nursing home and asked him where she was living. He didn’t tell them. They said, “No worries. We’ll do some digging and find out.” Contact tracing is here with a vengeance. Avoid getting tested if at all possible, unless you want to end up caught up in this web of government intrusion.

The physical properties of a cloth mask, reuse, the frequency and effectiveness of cleaning, and increased moisture retention, may potentially increase the infection risk for HCWs. Self-contamination through repeated use and improper removal is possible. For example, a contaminated cloth mask may transfer pathogen from the mask to the bare hands of the wearer. We also showed that filtration was extremely poor (almost 0%) for the cloth masks. Observations during SARS suggested double-masking and other practices increased the risk of infection because of moisture, liquid diffusion and pathogen retention. These effects may be associated with cloth masks.
